HEADWORD: Gasserian
<hw>Gas*se"ri*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Relating to
Casserio (L. <it>Gasserius</it>), the discover of the Gasserian
ganglion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Gasserian ganglion</b></col> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>, <cd>a
large ganglion, at the root of the trigeminal, or fifth cranial,
nerve.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

